               <p>93. <persName id="def1-93-18671216" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-93-18671216" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-93-18671216" type="age" value="28"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-93-18671216" type="surname" value="WEBB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-93-18671216" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">THOMAS WEBB</hi> (28)</persName> was indicted<rs id="t18671216-93-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18671216-93-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="breakingPeace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18671216-93-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="wounding"></interp> for unlawfully assaulting <persName id="t18671216-name-220" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-220" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-220" type="surname" value="COLLINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-220" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18671216-93-offence-1 t18671216-name-220"></join>Frederick Collins</persName> and causing him actual bodily harm.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. RIBTON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">CUNNINGHAM</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution, and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DALY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">the Defence.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18671216-name-221" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-221" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-221" type="surname" value="COLLINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-221" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK COLLINS</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">The evidence given by this witness in the last case was read over</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you see the whole of this transaction? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, decidedly not; not in the public-house, in the street—I was there when Thompson and Webb came up—I was a few yards from the other two—I saw Webb and Thompson come across the road, and Webb knocked me down—I had not spoken to him—no one was with me when I was knocked down—I was some distance from the others—I told Webb that he had made a mistake, that I had not insulted him—I did not say a word to them before they struck me, or do anything to them—I said nothing about fighting—I never spoke.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. RIBTON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Are you quite certain you did not say anything to them, or any of the others? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not a word; I had just bid Dear and the deceased good night—I believe they had got about four or five yards away—I was coming towards the corner when I saw the two men come across the road—they were three or four yards, it might be, from me when I first saw them; I was the first man knocked down.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did anybody say anything to them in your hearing? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did not hear a word, no more than what was said in the public-house—all three of us were in the public-house before they came in—we left them there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18671216-name-222" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-222" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-222" type="surname" value="MELVILLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-222" type="given" value="FRANCIS HENRY"></interp>FRANCIS HENRY MELVILLE</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">This witness's evidence in the last case was read over</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> What distance were you from the place? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> When I first heard it about twenty yards—I was within two yards of Webb</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186712160048"></xptr>
               <p>when he was walking away—I did not see Webb do anything, only scrambling off the man—I describe him as "the short man"—I could not swear it was Webb—it was a short man answering his description—I could not recognise the man only by seeing him afterwards—I could not swear he was the actual man that got off him—it was a short man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">The evidence of John Possnett was also read over.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18671216-name-223" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-223" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-223" type="surname" value="DEAR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-223" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DEAR</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">This witness's evidence was read over</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you see Webb do anything? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, I did not—I did not see him strike anybody—I do not know who struck me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18671216-name-224" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-224" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-224" type="surname" value="PIERCEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671216-name-224" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN PIERCEY</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">This witness's former evidence was read over</hi>). When I first saw Webb he was coming from the Swan—Thompson was with him—I did not see both of them go up to the three men—only one, that was Thompson—I lost sight of Webb—what he was doing then I don't know.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DALY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">proposed to call for the defence the prisoner Thompson, who had just been convicted.</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">MR. JUSTICE LUSH</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">doubted whether a felon under sentence of death was an admissible witness, and asked if</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DALY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">had any authority for the course he proposed to take.</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DALY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">had no direct authority, but he conceived that under Lord Denman's Act (6 and 7 Vict.), such a course was authorised.</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">MR. JUSTICE LUSH</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">considered the witness not a competent one. A person under sentence of death stood in a different position from an ordinary felon. Under the old law a person attainted and sentenced to death was deemed civilly dead, and he did not think his capacity as a witness was restored by 6 and 7 Vict.; he could not therefore receive the evidence, but if it became necessary would reserve the question.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18671216-93-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
